article.headline: Middle Tennessee 65, Indiana St. 58
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Kevin Kanaskie led a balanced scoring attack with 17 points as Middle Tennessee held off Indiana State 65-58 Thursday. Tim Blue added 14 points for the Blue Raiders (3-4) while Desmond Yates had 11 and Kyle Young 10, including 5-of-7 from the floor. Indiana State (4-2), which led 23-22 at halftime, got 16 points from Gabe Moore and 12 from Marico Stinson. Middle Tennessee shot 50 percent from the floor while the visitors hit 40 percent. Blue had a team-high 11 rebounds. Jay Tunnell had 11 for the Sycamores.
